<header class="header">
  <h1>Best Seed Company for Short Season Gardens</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    In short seasons, finishing matters more than starting.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most gardeners, Johnny’s Selected Seeds and West Coast Seeds are the best choices for short season gardens because they make it easier to find varieties that mature quickly and reliably. High Mowing Organic Seeds is a strong alternative when consistency matters across changing conditions.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Short growing seasons limit what you can grow, but more importantly, they limit what will actually finish.
  </p>
  <p>
    That makes seed selection one of the most important decisions you can make.
  </p>
</header>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Quick Picks: Best Seed Companies for Short Seasons</h2>

  <div class="quickAnswerBox">
    <ul class="plainList">
      <li><strong>Best overall:</strong> Johnny’s Selected Seeds — best for comparing maturity and choosing fast, reliable varieties.</li>
      <li><strong>Best for cool climates:</strong> West Coast Seeds — strong alignment with shorter, lower-heat seasons.</li>
      <li><strong>Best organic option:</strong> High Mowing Organic Seeds — consistent performance across variable conditions.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p>
    The best seed company is the one that helps you choose crops that will actually reach harvest in your available window.
  </p>
