<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most People Get Wrong</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>They choose crops that take too long.</strong> Not all vegetables are suited to short seasons.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They ignore maturity timing.</strong> Days to maturity is one of the most important factors.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They assume all varieties perform similarly.</strong> Small differences can determine success or failure.
  </p>
</section>

